         <abstract>
            <p>We consider the so-called Babuska method of finite elements with Lagrange multipliers for numerically solving the problem $\Delta u = f$ in $\Omega, u = g$ on $\partial \Omega, \Omega \subset R^n, n \geqslant 2$. We state a number of local conditions from which we prove the uniform stability of the Lagrange multiplier method in terms of a weighted, mesh-dependent norm. The stability conditions given weaken the conditions known so far and allow mesh refinements on the boundary. As an application, we introduce a class of finite element schemes, for which the stability conditions are satisfied, and we show that the convergence rate of these schemes is of optimal order.</p>
          </abstract>
